Project: AI Auto Facebook Messenger System
What It Does (Current MVP)
A Node.js/Express backend that connects Facebook Business Pages to an n8n automation workflow. The flow is:

A client visits your app and clicks "Connect with Facebook"
They authorize via Facebook OAuth — your app gets their Page access token
You store the Page token in Supabase PostgreSQL
When a customer messages that Facebook Page, Meta sends a webhook to your server
Your server forwards the message payload (sender ID, text, page token) to an n8n workflow
n8n handles the reply logic (e.g. GPT-powered auto-reply via Messenger API)
Current Stack
Layer	Tech
Runtime	Node.js (CommonJS)
Framework	Express v5
Database	PostgreSQL via Supabase (pg pool)
HTTP Client	Axios
Automation	n8n (external, Railway-hosted)
OAuth	Facebook Graph API v19.0
Dev tunnel	ngrok
