Prompt for an AI Coding Agent
Here's a ready-to-use brief you can give to another agent:

Build a production-ready Facebook Messenger Automation SaaS backend, expanding on this prototype:

Core concept: Multi-tenant system where each "client" connects one or more Facebook Pages. When a customer messages a connected Page, the system forwards the message to an n8n webhook so the automation can reply via Messenger API.

Tech stack: Node.js (ESM or CommonJS), Express or Fastify, PostgreSQL (Supabase), Axios, Facebook Graph API v19.0+.

Features to build:

OAuth flow (/auth/login → /auth/callback) — Facebook OAuth with scopes: pages_manage_metadata, pages_messaging, pages_read_engagement. After callback, fetch all user Pages via /me/accounts and let the user pick which page to connect (not just auto-pick the first one). Store user_id, page_id, page_name, page_token in a clients table.

Webhook handler (GET /webhook for verification, POST /webhook for messages) — On each incoming message, look up which client owns that page_id, then forward { sender_id, recipient_id, message_text, timestamp, page_token } to the client's configured n8n_webhook_url. Always respond 200 immediately to Meta.

Subscription code system — subscription_codes table with code, client_id, is_valid, expires_at. Endpoint to generate a code for a client, endpoint to validate a code (check DB, check expiry, mark used).

Client management API — CRUD endpoints: list clients, get one client, update n8n webhook URL per client, disconnect (delete) a client.

Admin dashboard (optional but valuable) — Simple HTML/React UI showing connected clients, their pages, last activity, subscription status.

Structured error handling — Try/catch on all async routes, proper HTTP status codes, JSON error responses, retry logic (3 attempts with backoff) when forwarding to n8n fails.

Logging — Use Winston or Pino. Log every webhook event, every forwarded message, every OAuth step.

Rate limiting — Express rate limiter on all API endpoints, stricter limit on webhook endpoint.

Database migrations — Use db-migrate or knex for schema versioning instead of hardcoded CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS.

Environment config — All secrets via .env (FB_APP_ID, FB_APP_SECRET, REDIRECT_URI, VERIFY_TOKEN, DATABASE_URL, PORT). Validate required vars on startup.

DB schema (reference):


clients(id, user_id, user_token, page_id, page_name, page_token, n8n_webhook_url, created_at)
subscription_codes(id, code, client_id, is_valid, created_at, expires_at)
